div.div:
Haskell uses a hybrid threading model, where threads can be
OS-level threads or green threads. See the docs for forkIO and forkOS. We use the TaskPool effect for parallelism, on top of forkIO, which is a
green-threaded model (haskell refers to this as unbound threads, or lightweight threads).
